8:
Nothing worth doing is ever easy,
huh?
11: But I'll never get stronger at this rate—
23:
...This is good. Is this what you offer
to royal visitors?
27:
N-no, uh... It's a pretty basic meal, 
to be honest. Easy to make.
32:
You are full of surprises. I should
know better than to underestimate
your repertoire of skills.
36:
Cooking's not THAT big of a deal... It's
mostly in the ingredients you pick—
39:
Ah... But you probably never had
that luxury...
44:
I hail from a barren place, far
different from other worlds...
49:
You... knew about Stella and them,
right?
51:
The ones you called the Overlords...
How much do you know about them?
56:
There was once a war—a great war.
Worlds collided, chaos reigned... All
to determine who would become
the ruler.
59:
The Overlords emerged victorious,
and all the worlds belonged to
them. They created the Star
Goddess and the Purger...
61:
And banished the fiends who lost to
Pandemonium.
64:
...There are no records of this history.
I learned all from that woman.
70:
One thing is for certain: the
Overlords exist. Not as an ancient
legend or vanished civilization... 
But as a real, current threat.
73: Alk. What do you intend to do?
78:
Whatever I can to stop them. My
mind's been made up about this for
a while now.
80:
I'm not sure how much help I'll be,
but you can count on me giving it
my all.
82:
...Not that we can do anything but
wait at the moment.
87: Then our paths are the same.
94:
I will also do all I can, so that my
people may have a future.
96: Take me with you on your journey.
104:
I mean, I'm fine with it, but maybe
we should grab Stella and Light's
opinions—
107:
Why? I am asking you. Not the
goddess. Not the Purger. You.
112:
In that case... Welcome aboard! 
I couldn't ask for a more capable ally.
117:
But make sure you give Stella and
Light a proper heads-up, okay?
123:
First, however, I'd like to have a
promise fulfilled.
132:
Morning, Stella. You doing good
today?
136:
Good morning. I am.
What are Claw, Albert, and
Adjudicus doing?
139:
Seems like Lilith's world is running
out of living space again.
142:
I figured Claw and Albert would be
the ones with the best advice, and
well... They've been at it since early
morning.
145:
Discussing a whole bunch of stuff,
like how to get along with humans
and where to migrate to.
150:
Yo! Morning, Stella! Have you met
this guy? He's real interesting!
152:
We hit it off, then he suddenly
started talking about economics.
Value of currency and all that!
155:
There must be worlds out there that
operate on credit. Employment
would be more stable in such a
system.
159:
Hm... The authorities in charge
wouldn't be for it though... A forced
implementation would likewise be
out of the question.
169:
Yeah... I've got no clue what they're
saying.
172:
But... I've got a good feeling
everything will work out.
